title: Marine File Snake (Acrochordus granulatus)
description: is a snake species found from India through Southeast Asia to the Solomon Islands. It is completely aquatic and almost helpless on land

title: Painted Bronzeback (Dendrelaphis pictus)

title: Southern Triangle-spotted Snake(Cyclocorus nuchalis)
description: commonly known as the southern triangle-spotted snake, is a species of snake in the family Cyclocoridae. It is native to southern Philippines.[1][2]

title: Northern Triangle-spotted Snake (Cyclocorus lineatus)
description: commonly known as Reinhardt's lined snake, is a species of snake in the family Lamprophiidae. It is endemic to the Philippines.

description: is a species of a colubrid snake native to coastal waters of Asia and Australia.

description: also known as the New Guinea bockadam, South Asian bockadam, bockadam snake, or dog-faced water snake, is a mildly venomous species

title: Tropidonophis negrosensis()
description: Tropidonophis negrosensis, the Negros spotted water snake, is a species of colubrid snake. It is found in the Philippines

title: Blunthead Slug Snake(Aplopeltura boa)
description: single species, Aplopeltura boa, the blunthead slug snake or blunt-headed slug-eating snake. It is a small, non-venomous snake. The species can be found in southern Thailand, Malaysia, Indonesia, Brunei and the Philippines.

title: White-striped Snake(Sibynophis bivittatus)

title: Boie's Keelback(Rhabdophis spilogaster)
description: commonly known as the northern water snake or Boie's keelback, is a keelback snake in the family Colubridae found in the Philippines on the islands of Catanduanes, Polillo, Calayan and in the province of Bataan on the island of Luzon.
